", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"the committee chairship\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"etc\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"presidents\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"the chair\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"the finance committee\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 742}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of note also, is a pact of sorts between Gabriel Attal - now leader of the Macronist party, and Laurent Wauquiez - leader of the centrist Republicans.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9998635936559064, \"rank\": 0.00013361237032698205, \"text\": \"Republicans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a pact\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"sorts\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"the Macronist party\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"Laurent Wauquiez - leader\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 866}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wauquiez is seen by many of the centre right as a potential presidential hopeful.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 977, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wauquiez\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"a potential presidential hopeful\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 976}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The close relationship between them, points to an emerging ploy which to paraphase the former Interior minister Gerard Darmanin aims to 'to break the socialists away from the NFP'.\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7639182667365908e-23, \"text\": \"Interior minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 1091, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barksdale_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9993079690949, \"rank\": 0.0006921843463602832, \"text\": \"Gerard\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barksdale_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barksdale_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 1129, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialism\", \"score\": 0.5150124471160095, \"rank\": 0.8016368027170513, \"text\": \"socialists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialism\"}, {\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999953416392418, \"rank\": 3.840724037003097e-06, \"text\": \"NFP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Federation_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The close relationship\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"an emerging ploy\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1042}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that was to happen, then there is a good chance that France can have a centrist coalition spanning left to right (amidst plenty of personal and policy disagreements).\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.7508499543511039, \"rank\": 0.3293653420772698, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good chance\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1210}, {\"ngram\": \"a centrist coalition\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"right\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"personal and policy disagreements\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before that happens, there needs to be a mini-crisis - possibly around economic policy - where the La France Insoumise - can be discredited.\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mini\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"crisis\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"economic policy\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"the La France Insoumise\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This points to more volatility.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This points\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"more volatility\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As it stands, the NFT group is trying to come up with a unified proposal for prime minister (official it is the president who picks the PM).\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Non-fungible_token\", \"score\": 0.9999988353276837, \"rank\": 1.1646735898122333e-06, \"text\": \"NFT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Non-fungible_token\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Non-fungible_token\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a unified proposal\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1575}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"the PM\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1641}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile the RN (Rassemblement) remain marginalised and are positioning themselves as the party of the people (versus the elites).\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the RN\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"(Rassemblement\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"the party\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1741}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"the elites\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In sum, the formation of a durable government will take more time, potentially to late August, and may also require more volatility.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1910, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sum\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"the formation\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"a durable government\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"more time\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1843}, {\"ngram\": \"late August\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"more volatility\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A centrist coalition is a possibility, the issue is what kind of political strife is required to fuse it.\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A centrist coalition\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"a possibility\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1948}, {\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"what kind\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"political strife\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the meantime, the Olympics (and summer holidays) will take centre stage in France.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.7508499543511039, \"rank\": 0.3293653420772698, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the meantime\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2032}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"summer holidays\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"centre stage\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2091}]}]}"